{
  "stem": "1061.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I guess it was because it came from an individual, a single individual woman.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It wasn't the German with the dog who hit me with his-- I was once hit on the-- during quarantine.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had a big gold ring, and he hit me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember how blood splattered.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean this, I didn't-- this was par for the course.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "To be hit in the face and to bleed profusely is one thing-- by a dog-- by a gentleman with a dog.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But to have Aranka pick me and-- and stand over me, threatening me to clean her shoes, that struck me as something totally-- And it's ridiculous, really.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, if you considered whole picture, this was really nothing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this isn't even worth remembering.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I do remember things like that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, among each other.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Among the prisoners, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were very attached to the group because, as I told you, these were still people from our hometown, you see.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we worked in those marshes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know how long, but then a call came for 30 women to be sent to another job.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were picked.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "As I told you, we had the three numbers in consecutive order.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the numbers were called, and we were sent to a job.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, that was a godsend.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That saved our lives, really, because it was an indoor job.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was within the Auschwitz camp, but it was a-- it was a unit of-- of-- that was self-containing unit, separated from the population-- Auschwitz speculation-- from the camp.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It used to be called-- it was called a [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it dealt with clothing of political prisoners who-- you know, I'm not talking about Jews now.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, Auschwitz was also a camp-- aside from being a killing camp for the Jews, it was also a camp, a concentration camp, for prisoners of other nationalities and other faiths.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when these prisoners would be sent into Auschwitz, their-- their clothes would be put in bags and hung up with numbers and so on.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Every time they would be transferred-- to Buchenwald or whatever-- the bags had to be shipped out.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And if they died, the bags were shipped to the families in Poland or wherever.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well, apparently, there was something going on there politically.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It-- this particular unit was run by Polish-- Christian Polish prisoners-- women, political prisoners.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Apparently there was some connection with the Polish underground.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Whatever it was, they took away the women who were suspected, and they decided to substitute it with these Jewish women picked from the camp.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Well, we were the lucky ones.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because this was now indoor labor, and it wasn't really labor.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I learned how to pack there, because we had to pack and repack.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "All I know is that we still were sent back to camp to stay overnight and then back.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And after awhile, they decided that they didn't want us going back to camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So we really stayed in that unit.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the food was a little better-- wasn't much, but it was-- whatever it was, was twice a day, again, but it-- we could keep a little cleaner because we didn't sleep nine to a bunk.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I don't know, maybe we sleep-- slept three to a bunk.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I really don't remember-- but certainly not nine.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] having now worked in the marshes-- and this is the fall-- you see, the fall season.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "By now, it's about October, maybe November.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Having gotten out of those marshes, you can imagine what stroke of luck this was to find ourselves under a roof, not standing in water, not being beaten on the marches.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Because the march itself, going from the Auschwitz barrack to that-- to the marshes, that also took its toll because people were being shot on the way and coming back.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we didn't have to march to the work-- to the job, because the job was there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We slept indoors.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We worked indoors.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think this is really, in the final analysis, this phase would have finished us off-- although a lot of women from our hometown did survive.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because after-- you see, we were in that [GERMAN] unit until they were liquidating Auschwitz, which was about two months.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And a lot of women who did not go with us and did join us on that death march later survived-- as I am here to attest, because I see some of them once a year when we meet for the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, everybody knows what happened when the death march occurred.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you know, Auschwitz was evacuated on the 18th-- officially on the 18th of January 1945.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
